$\begin{align}
y\,\dfrac{\text{liters}}{\text{minute}}\cdot 0.2\,\dfrac{\text{dollars}}{\text{liter}}=x\,\dfrac{\text{dollars}}{\text{minute}}
\end{align}$

So in order to find  $x$, the cost per minute, we need to figure out the value of $y$, which is the rate of liters used per minute of shower.

