\end{align}$

Now we can plug that in the original equation:

$\begin{align}
0.15\,\dfrac{\text{liter}}{\text{minute}}\cdot 0.2\,\dfrac{\text{dollars}}{\text{liter}}&=x\,\dfrac{\text{dollars}}{\text{minute}}
\\\\
0.03\,\dfrac{\text{dollars}}{\text{minute}}&=x\,\dfrac{\text{dollars}}{\text{minute}}
\end{align}$

